article.headline: Cal Poly 90, Cal State Fullerton 80
article.story: ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- Derek Stockalper had 18 points and nine rebounds to lead Cal Poly to an 81-56 rout of Cal State Fullerton on Friday night in the semifinals of the Big West Conference tournament. Trae Clark added 16 points and Chaz Thomas had 14 points for the second-seeded Mustangs (19-10), who will face top-seeded Long Beach State in Saturday night's championship. Cal Poly earned its eighth consecutive victory and 13th win in 15 games. Scott Cutley had 20 points and 10 rebounds for the third-seeded Titans (20-10), who shot a season-low 32.3 percent and ended the season with five losses in their final seven games. Fullerton's Bobby Brown added 11 points and finished his four-year career in ninth place on the Big West's career scoring list with 1,961 points. The Titans held a 13-12 lead when Cal Poly went on a 20-4 spree to move ahead 32-17 with 7:28 left in the first half. The Mustangs made seven of eight shots and scored nine points off turnovers. Fullerton narrowed its deficit to 36-28 at halftime but Cal Poly began the second half with a 16-2 surge to extend the lead to 52-30 with 14:33 to play. Clark scored six points and Stockalper added five during the run, as the Mustangs made six of eight shots. Cal Poly led by as many as 27 points.
